i can sorta understand the way he reacted. he was hurt by the people calling him a n00b... and in his mind he just had to try and make them understand. they rejected it. the rejection burned him up inside, and it got him *very* angry. so he tries to make these people look "evil" to fit into his reality. if you are bored, look up borderline personality disorder. its kinda interesting really. yet sad in the same way.. how its all caused by unstable childhoods, and the fact that the person believes theyll never ever be cared for, and arent worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uclanmcstump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClanMcStump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/14/01 6:38:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=711.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ---</span><hr size=1> The problem with diagnosing an adolescent with borderline personality disorder is that the majority of teenagers meet at least 2 or 3 of the criteria.<br>
<br>
For example, the definition you can find at dictionary.com:<br>
<br>
b)Relating to a condition characterized by a pattern of instability in mood, interpersonal relations, and self-image, and manifested by self-destructive, impulsive, and inconsistent behavior: the borderline syndrome. <br>
<br>
Granted, its not a great definition of the disorder, but since I dont carry around a DSM-IV with me, it'll have to do.<br>
<br>
How many teenagers do you know (or do you remember when you were a teenager) that have problems with mood, relationships, and self-image?  uhhh, most <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and as for myself, I may not have been destructive (well... not most of the time anyway) but you could definately have called my behavior inconsistent and impulsive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I would say, however, that Ghallunt does seem to have some issues, and the best way to get him some help would be to make the authorities in his area aware of the problem.  It may seem drastic, but I would rather see folks err on the side of caution than to see in the news that some kid in south florida walked into his school at the beginning of the new semester and started shooting people.<br>
